# QuickXerox Account FAQs & Support Guide

## User Profile Management

### Q: How do I update my profile details?
**A:** Go to the "My Account" page (`/account`) and click "Edit Profile". You can update your **Name**, **Mobile Number**, **Address**, **City**, **State**, and **Pincode**. 
*   **Note:** Changes are saved **instantly**. You do not need to refresh the page to see updates.

### Q: Why can't I change my Email Address?
**A:** The email field is **locked (read-only)**. This is by design to ensure the security of your account and to maintain a consistent link to your **Order History**. If you absolutely must change it, you would need to create a new account or contact support.

### Q: I saved my changes but they reverted back. Why?
**A:** This was a known issue that has been **fixed**. The system now updates its internal cache immediately upon saving. If you still encounter this, simply refresh the page to fetch the latest data from the server.

---

## Order History & Tracking

### Q: Why can't I see my past orders?
**A:** Order History is linked strictly to your **Email Address**.
1.  Verify that the email in your profile (`My Account`) matches the email you used when placing the orders.
2.  If you previously placed orders using only a mobile number (without an email associated), they might not appear in the new view. The system was recently updated to prioritize Email for better accuracy.

### Q: Does the system use my Mobile Number to find orders?
**A:** **No.** As of the latest update, the system relies on your **Email Address** (`customerEmail`) to fetch your order history. This is to prevent issues with mobile number formatting (e.g., `+91` prefix variations).

---

## Troubleshooting

### Q: I see an "Account Error" message saying "We couldn't load your profile setup".
**A:** This happens when your login session exists, but your profile data is incomplete or "ghosted" (empty).
*   **Fix:** Click the **"Sign Out & Try Again"** button on that screen. This will clear your session and allow you to log in freshly, which guarantees your profile is loaded correctly.

### Q: I see two "Success" notifications when I save my profile.
**A:** This has been resolved. You should now only see a single "Profile updated successfully!" notification.

### Q: The location finder is stuck on "Fetching location...".
**A:** We have optimized the location service. It now has a **10-second timeout**.
*   If it cannot find you within 10 seconds (e.g., GPS signal is weak), it will stop waiting and let you enter your location manually.
*   Your location is cached for **1 minute**, so reloading the page won't force you to wait again.
